{"sha": "d10b113b355a49aa2bb1552e96c48b19b7846c27", "node_id": "C_kwDOAAsO6NoAKGQxMGIxMTNiMzU1YTQ5YWEyYmIxNTUyZTk2YzQ4YjE5Yjc4NDZjMjc", "commit": {"author": {"name": "Alan Egerton", "email": "eggyal@gmail.com", "date": "2023-03-15T14:56:53Z"}, "committer": {"name": "Alan Egerton", "email": "eggyal@gmail.com", "date": "2023-03-15T14:57:59Z"}, "message": "Set CMAKE_SYSTEM_NAME for Linux targets\n\nWhen bootstrap compiles native dependencies like LLVM, it should set\nCMAKE_SYSTEM_NAME for the target system; otherwise cmake may not\nidentify that it is cross-compiling.\n\nIn particular, when building a Linux rustc on a macOS host, cmake was\nincluding `-isysroot /path/to/macOS.sdk` options that caused things to\nbreak.  By setting `CMAKE_SYSTEM_NAME=Linux` when building for Linux\ntargets, the macOS SDK is no longer passed as sysroot to the compiler.", "tree": {"sha": "2f4203d1781ba494b8140888c7b5df631db0f14b", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/git/trees/2f4203d1781ba494b8140888c7b5df631db0f14b"}, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/git/commits/d10b113b355a49aa2bb1552e96c48b19b7846c27", "comment_count": 0, "verification": {"verified": true, "reason": "valid", "signature": "-----BEGIN PGP SIGNATURE-----\n\niQJFBAABCAAvFiEEvrRBFuOXsbT1OVTHfUwvbCISJTIFAmQR3uIRHGVnZ3lhbEBn\nbWFpbC5jb20ACgkQfUwvbCISJTKXkw//RODU3VRbyMnmW2Tkli3ZFqEmsIKz9gEw\n9ztPPTirdRvkO7J9zK3JllS/soBrZf0pwyCl2Ko5m4ZGJtlpklr6Aa7K4ls9zTZg\nU6nVS9FITjXu0vu/opwXKToMu1kXbwU7Fmb/bXNVr6JZXESE0LJv36VCSPVY3HE/\nGORcdaVBQpdkdbOz3HokK4qE45lKtxYxJdfzBQVU+Mob/lCf0JojdDQV3vXo4hIo\nNMWrINEN/qZ2p6+snCAdueEeVTCIOreXcNggaGYGaIKF8DnZmXC3d9dCageJUKST\nLhXNtt7qMA5dWxenR6gcu1YsGbsw1JsTRPcV2/FPLBWatCbJOomHYTyT6oWe4uHh\n/TUuP4ofMrgPOs4rz1xMhzLo1E+15CyDX6ctQe3sRW+HsuFJ3uH3fIvPms9gneW6\nBLjL3tppIesXhCKzzWqV02GwsmgydTv3+TJmrLYfoD5Yr6t9jNqWXChxLAWexmO9\nrBuc/PmBrH+900DroEek03sSrZcGRbS0iBOi21SzeqtkMNXUptkp//nVDgcECa3n\nqMM21lqg+R7uHtV7Do4MjXlfzYLiU9V3WURyeRfuR1Od5ojzALv34Qvo+Fusc8pj\n7lXID9KwkTT1QvFIvPMExskvS5L0l0nxnISArphtacKfcpe6px+boiSaDSnbqEUj\nhZsXpyA3kOs=\n=3Hkf\n-----END PGP SIGNATURE-----", "payload": "tree 2f4203d1781ba494b8140888c7b5df631db0f14b\nparent e4b9f86054c581d931f8bad0c87523c53e1e8e3f\nauthor Alan Egerton <eggyal@gmail.com> 1678892213 +0000\ncommitter Alan Egerton <eggyal@gmail.com> 1678892279 +0000\n\nSet CMAKE_SYSTEM_NAME for Linux targets\n\nWhen bootstrap compiles native dependencies like LLVM, it should set\nCMAKE_SYSTEM_NAME for the target system; otherwise cmake may not\nidentify that it is cross-compiling.\n\nIn particular, when building a Linux rustc on a macOS host, cmake was\nincluding `-isysroot /path/to/macOS.sdk` options that caused things to\nbreak.  By setting `CMAKE_SYSTEM_NAME=Linux` when building for Linux\ntargets, the macOS SDK is no longer passed as sysroot to the compiler.\n"}}, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/commits/d10b113b355a49aa2bb1552e96c48b19b7846c27", "html_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/commit/d10b113b355a49aa2bb1552e96c48b19b7846c27", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/commits/d10b113b355a49aa2bb1552e96c48b19b7846c27/comments", "author": {"login": "eggyal", "id": 3089613, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjMwODk2MTM=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/3089613?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/eggyal", "html_url": "https://github.com/eggyal", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/eggyal/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/eggyal/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/eggyal/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/eggyal/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/eggyal/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/eggyal/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/eggyal/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/eggyal/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://a